post_text:
A note from Nurse Wells,

Hey there parents and students! As you all know, there will be many changes this school year. That also means that there are changes to the nurse's office procedures. I have updated my health services page on our school's website: http://www.nfranklin.k12.mo.us/programs/health-services

On this page, you will find my "virtual office" with clickable links. There are links to Coronavirus information from the CDC, as well as the nurse office procedures and pertinent forms that may be needed. Below the virtual office, you will see our school's procedure for contact tracing in the event that there is a positive case of COVID in our school, as well as a "Can My Student Come to School?" flow chart. I ask parents and students to please familiarize themselves with these changes. Please know that our school is doing all we can to keep our students and staff safe and healthy.

post_text:
Good evening Elementary Bulldog Families,

Just a couple of important bits of information. Class lists will be posted outside the elementary doors on Friday, August 14th after 8:15a.m. Please remember to practice social distancing while viewing the lists. Also, due to Covid-19 the only elementary classes having Open House are Preschool and kindergarten, by appointment only. Preschool and Kindergarten teachers will be calling parents to schedule a time to come in and meet the teacher and view his/her classroom. For students first through fifth grade, teachers will be sending out letters/and or calling the students to introduce themselves.

We truly appreciate your flexibility and patience during these unprecedented times. Together we are Bulldog Strong!!

post_text:
Our third 2020 retiree is Sherry Dennis! Congrats on your retirement, and thanks for all you have done for our district!

How many years have you worked in New Franklin?: "16 years"

What other districts have you worked with?: "Slater School District"

What is your favorite memory of your time in New Franklin?: "My favorite memories are working with the students and watching them develop and grow."

What will you miss most about being at New Franklin?: "The wonderful faculty and staff! They are truly fabulous caring people!"

What are you looking forward to most with retirement?: "I am getting married so I am excited to start a new chapter with someone wonderful and to be his wife, never getting up at 5am ever again, exploring new places, riding my bicycle, spending more time with family and friends, flower gardening, and walking Jake Mutley Hound-dog! I plan to just have fun and live everyday as if it is my last!"

2020 Senior Spotlight: Isaac Schupp

What is your favorite memory of hight school?: "Any time that I was hanging out with my friends."

What are your plans for after high school?: "I plan on going to CMU."

What is your favorite quote?: "Keep a cool head and maintain a low profile. Never take the lead, but aim to do something big." --Deng Xiaoping

How would you like to be remembered once you leave NFHS?: "The quiet one."

"What are three items that are on your "bucket list"?: "Go to college, graduate college, make money."

Whom do you admire? "My older brother Jacob."

What will you miss most about high school?: "Pretty much everything except homework."

post_text:
2020 Senior Spotlight: Jack Woods

Nicknames: Baymax

Extracurricular Activities: Choir (3 years)

Post-High School Plans: “Go to trade school for welding”

Favorite Memory of High School: “Mr. Early’s class”

How would you like to be remembered once you leave NFHS?: “Kind”

What will you most miss about high school?: “The people”

What is your favorite quote: “Whether you think you can or you think you can't, you’re right” -Henry Ford

If you were told you couldn’t graduate unless you could prove your achievements from the past four years, what three examples would you use?: “Staying in school, getting a job, and paying my bills.”

What are three items on your "bucket list"?: “Skydive, see the ocean, and sail the ocean”

Who do you admire, and why?: “My Dad, because he will go out of his way to help someone.”

Who has given you the best advice? What did they say?: “Work smarter, not harder”-Adam

post_text:
2020 Senior Spotlight: Haley Washburn

Nicknames: Washburn, H-Dub, Haley Dub

Extracurricular Activities: Band (4 years), Softball (2 years), Cheerleading (2 years), Dance (2 years), Choir (1 year), FBLA (1 year)

Post-High School Plans: 4 year college majoring in Pre-Med

Favorite Memory of High School: “Cheering on the boys to their back-to-back district championships.”

How would you like to be remembered once you leave NFHS?: “I would like to be remembered as the funny, nice girl.”

What will you most miss about high school?: “All my friends and the teachers.”

What is your favorite quote: ““You know, I’ve realized that I’m probably just perfect and it’s everybody else around me that’s got issues.” - Scott Disick

What are three items on your "bucket list"?: “Meet Harry Styles, own a G-Wagon, and travel the world.”

Who do you admire, and why?: “I admire my mother. She works her hardest to make sure all of us children have the best of things. She always makes sure we feel loved and cared for.”

2020 Senior Spotlight: Haley Washburn

Nicknames: Washburn, H-Dub, Haley Dub

Extracurricular Activities: Band (4 years), Softball (2 years), Cheerleading (2 years), Dance (2 years), Choir (1 year), FBLA (1 year)

Post-High School Plans: 4 year college majoring in Pre-Med

Favorite Memory of High School: “Cheering on the boys to their back-to-back district championships.”

How would you like to be remembered once you leave NFHS?: “I would like to be remembered as the funny, nice girl.”

What will you most miss about high school?: “All my friends and the teachers.”

What is your favorite quote: ““You know, I’ve realized that I’m probably just perfect and it’s everybody else around me that’s got issues.” - Scott Disick

What are three items on your "bucket list"?: “Meet Harry Styles, own a G-Wagon, and travel the world.”

Who do you admire, and why?: “I admire my mother. She works her hardest to make sure all of us children have the best of things. She always makes sure we feel loved and cared for.”

post_text:
SURPRISE!! Some of our seniors were surprised at home today by a parade of teachers and staff members. They were presented with a yard sign to help show how much they all mean to us. However, the best part was, after nearly 6 weeks, getting to reconnect with some or our students (while maintaining social distancing of course). This is a special group of seniors, and they will be remembered long after this pandemic has passed.

And a special thinks to Mr. Dorson for setting the whole thing up!

Hiring for Database Manager
New Franklin R-1 School District is accepting applications for a student information and database manager. The applicant should have effective communication and interpersonal skills and possess technology skills that include working with our student information system and lunch programs. This position provides a full spectrum of administrative support to the school principals and staff including matters of a confidential nature. It will be a 10-month position and pay between $13-$16 per hour depending on skills and experience plus health and life insurance benefits. Applications may be secured at the school website www.nfranklin.k12.mo.us. The New Franklin R-1 School District is an Equal Opportunity Employer.

Preschool screening is scheduled for Thursday, March 5, 2020 from 8:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. This screening is for all children in the district who will be at least three years old before August 1, 2020. Screenings are by appointment only. Appointments may be made by calling the elementary office at 848-2112. We strongly encourage parents who are interested in sending their child to Ready Set Grow Preschool to have their child participate in this screening. Please tell any families you know that have 3 or 4 year old children about screening!

New Franklin HS Cheerleading is with Christina Fischer.
February 13 at 12:20 PM ·

Tuesday night we held our 4th Annual Pink Night game! I cannot say thank you enough to everyone who donated, helped decorate, and put in time to make this night amazing as usual. The silent auction was the largest we have ever had, and the items were all taken home by members of the community. At the end of the night our grand total for our donation to Ellis Fischel Cancer Center was over $2,500!! Once again the amount of support I receive is unmeasurable, and I will continue to love holding this event every year. 🎀💙🐾

Please register your students online for the Cherrydale Fundraiser! The more who register and send emails out to family and friends; the more our school gains for the classroom, field trips and the playground!

Ordering Instructions:

Best Option: Online @ ShopFund.com with ship to home options. Do not write online orders on your order form. Orders over $75 offer free shipping to your home.

Great Option: Text PAY to 555888 to pay with a credit card. Do not write text-to-pay orders on your order form.

Good Option: Share the catalog with family, friends and neighbors. Input the orders on your order form and collect payment (cash or check).

The TOP CLASS with the highest percentage of participation and has their orders and money turned in on time will have a PIZZA PARTY!

The TOP CLASS with the highest average number of retail sales dollars and has their orders and money turned in on time will have a PIZZA PARTY!

Thank you to all who participate! We truly appreciate you!

New Franklin students entering grade 6 are encouraged to attend one orientation session that will take place on Monday, August 5. Orientation sessions will begin at 9 am, 10 am, 1 pm, and 2 pm. Please select one that suits your family best. At orientation you will visit with the Middle School Counselor and Principal, receive your class schedule and locker assignment, take a tour of the middle and high school building, and have the opportunity to organize your school supplies in your locker. We prefer that a parent or guardian is present for each student. Again, new 6th graders will have orientations on Monday, August 5th beginning at 9 am, 10 am, 1 pm, and 2 pm. If you are unable to make any of these, please call office to schedule an alternative time.

John Franklin
July 30, 2019 at 10:46 AM ·

This is Ms. Shipp your elementary principal. I'm excited to start the 2019-20 school year. I want to take this opportunity to let you know about a few important upcoming dates. Class lists will be posted at the elementary entrance on Wednesday, August 7th at 8:00 a.m.
Open house will be held from 4:00 to 6:00 p.m. on Monday August 12th. I hope to see all families here that evening. The first day of school will be Wednesday, August 14th. If you know of any new families in our district with elementary children, please encourage them to contact the elementary office at 660 848-2112 to start the enrollment process. please don't hesitate to contact the office with any questions, or visit the school web page at www.nfranklin.k12.mo.us. I'm looking forward to an amazing school year! See you at Open House.

The Northeast Region Executive Committee of the Missouri State Teachers Association would like to acknowledge and congratulate Matt Wells for being nominated as a "Friend of Education" for the New Franklin R-1 School District. Matt was nominated by the district CTA chapter that is made up of New Franklin faculty and staff. Matt Wells was nominated for his positive attitude and relationship with students. He goes above and beyond to build a relationship with each student while still being able to complete his daily job. The Executive Committee of the Northeast M.S.T.A. is proud to present grateful recognition to this nominee for their dedication and commitment to academic excellence and continued efforts to enhance public education for the students of schools in our area. Without this type of support and dedication for our school systems, a well-rounded education would be much more difficult to achieve. Thanks once again for their commitment to education.

shared_text:
John Franklin
March 12, 2019 at 7:23 AM ·

The Kindergarten Screening at New Franklin Elementary School is scheduled Tuesday, March 19th from 8:00 A.M.- 6:00 P.M. Children who will be five years of age prior to August 1, 2019 should participate in this screening to be eligible for kindergarten next fall. Please bring with you to the screening your child’s birth certificate, immunization record, social security card, and proof of residency in the school district. Proof of residency is not necessary if you have older children already enrolled in the district. Items accepted for proof of residency include: rental contract, real estate contract signed by all parties, utility bill, payroll check, driver’s license, or W-4 form. The screening is done by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please call the elementary office at 848-2112 to schedule an appointment.
